Wayne Bridge: &quot;Chelsea are definitely capable of challenging, 100%. I would like to think they go and win it. They're contenders, I think they look good. Mourinho looks like he's his old self again, but I don't want Spurs to win it. I played for Chelsea, it's Spurs isn't it&quot;<br />
Bridge: &quot;Most people don't want to see Spurs win it to be honest. I'd love to see Lamps win it, and he's got a great chance. The squad they've got, and don't forget a lot of these players only signed this year and it does take a while to settle.&quot;
